{"type":"message","id":"29426baa","parentId":"48b72a6c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:55:01.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qyZXpzLJccgZAwAY8W9SwtH2|fc_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4d47197248196ad140ef69649b7a7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S5\\S5_SCENE_KIT_OBJECTS_V1.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## 6. `scene_editorial_input` (conceptual V1 package)\n\n## 6.1 Role\n\nThis is the effective package S7 consumes.\n\nIt may or may not be implemented as one physical file, but conceptually it should include everything needed for scene-level editorial resolution.\n","newText":"## 6. `scene_editorial_input` (conceptual V1 package)\n\n## 6.1 Role\n\nThis is the effective package S7 consumes.\n\n`scene_editorial_input` should currently be understood as a **conceptual downstream package**, not necessarily as a single canonical on-disk artifact.\n\nIt may eventually be implemented as:\n- one compiled artifact\n- a structured bundle of multiple artifacts\n- or a runtime-composed package assembled from several persisted sources\n\nFor V1, the important point is not file singularity.\nThe important point is that S7 must receive a coherent editorial input surface rather than a disconnected set of files.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S5\\\\S5_SCENE_KIT_OBJECTS_V1.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## 6. `scene_editorial_input` (conceptual V1 package)\\n\\n## 6.1 Role\\n\\nThis is the effective package S7 consumes.\\n\\nIt may or may not be implemented as one physical file, but conceptually it should include everything needed for scene-level editorial resolution.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## 6. `scene_editorial_input` (conceptual V1 package)\\n\\n## 6.1 Role\\n\\nThis is the effective package S7 consumes.\\n\\n`scene_editorial_input` should currently be understood as a **conceptual downstream package**, not necessarily as a single canonical on-disk artifact.\\n\\nIt may eventually be implemented as:\\n- one compiled artifact\\n- a structured bundle of multiple artifacts\\n- or a runtime-composed package assembled from several persisted sources\\n\\nFor V1, the important point is not file singularity.\\nThe important point is that S7 must receive a coherent editorial input surface rather than a disconnected set of files.\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":218,"output":269,"cacheRead":96640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97127,"cost":{"input":0.000545,"output":0.004035,"cacheRead":0.024159999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028739999999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775555689406,"responseId":"resp_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4d46bde848196881ffcd7269b4ebc"}}
