{"type":"message","id":"17545803","parentId":"ce41962c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:23:50.897Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dKJ9GkH63oqziZp9hH0HF3Ie|fc_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4db2f3b7081968e3591720e6786d4","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S5\\S5_SCENE_KIT_BOUNDARY_CONCEPT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### 9.3 Prefer budget-aware scene kits over idealized unlimited kits\n\nS5 must not design kits in a vacuum.\n\nIf S5 asks for too many assets, too much motion, or too many expensive modes, S6 becomes impractical.\n\nTherefore V1 must include explicit production boundaries such as:\n- allowed generation modes\n- kit complexity ceiling\n- motion budget or motion allowed flag\n- baseline asset count expectations\n","newText":"### 9.3 Prefer budget-aware scene kits over idealized unlimited kits\n\nS5 must not design kits in a vacuum.\n\nIf S5 asks for too many assets, too much motion, or too many expensive modes, S6 becomes impractical.\n\nTherefore V1 must include explicit production boundaries such as:\n- allowed generation modes\n- kit complexity ceiling\n- a simple motion policy\n- baseline asset count expectations\n\nFor V1, motion should be handled through a deterministic system rule rather than open-ended LLM choice.\nThe current preferred policy is:\n- `motion_policy: first_10_scenes_only`\n- scenes with index `<= 10` receive `motion_allowed = true`\n- scenes after that receive `motion_allowed = false`\n\nThis should be injected by the substrate or boundary logic rather than freely invented by S5.\n"},{"oldText":"- allowed generation modes\n- whether motion is allowed and at what budget level\n","newText":"- allowed generation modes\n- whether motion is allowed under the active deterministic motion policy\n"},{"oldText":"- `motion_allowed`\n- `motion_budget`\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\n","newText":"- `motion_policy`\n- `motion_allowed` (injected deterministically per scene rather than freely authored by the LLM)\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S5\\\\S5_SCENE_KIT_BOUNDARY_CONCEPT.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### 9.3 Prefer budget-aware scene kits over idealized unlimited kits\\n\\nS5 must not design kits in a vacuum.\\n\\nIf S5 asks for too many assets, too much motion, or too many expensive modes, S6 becomes impractical.\\n\\nTherefore V1 must include explicit production boundaries such as:\\n- allowed generation modes\\n- kit complexity ceiling\\n- motion budget or motion allowed flag\\n- baseline asset count expectations\\n\",\"newText\":\"### 9.3 Prefer budget-aware scene kits over idealized unlimited kits\\n\\nS5 must not design kits in a vacuum.\\n\\nIf S5 asks for too many assets, too much motion, or too many expensive modes, S6 becomes impractical.\\n\\nTherefore V1 must include explicit production boundaries such as:\\n- allowed generation modes\\n- kit complexity ceiling\\n- a simple motion policy\\n- baseline asset count expectations\\n\\nFor V1, motion should be handled through a deterministic system rule rather than open-ended LLM choice.\\nThe current preferred policy is:\\n- `motion_policy: first_10_scenes_only`\\n- scenes with index `<= 10` receive `motion_allowed = true`\\n- scenes after that receive `motion_allowed = false`\\n\\nThis should be injected by the substrate or boundary logic rather than freely invented by S5.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- allowed generation modes\\n- whether motion is allowed and at what budget level\\n\",\"newText\":\"- allowed generation modes\\n- whether motion is allowed under the active deterministic motion policy\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- `motion_allowed`\\n- `motion_budget`\\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\\n\",\"newText\":\"- `motion_policy`\\n- `motion_allowed` (injected deterministically per scene rather than freely authored by the LLM)\\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":263,"output":444,"cacheRead":109568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110275,"cost":{"input":0.0006575000000000001,"output":0.00666,"cacheRead":0.027392,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0347095}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775557408058,"responseId":"resp_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4db23927081968f2637a0386be76e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"31bd9e92","parentId":"17545803","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:23:51.253Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dKJ9GkH63oqziZp9hH0HF3Ie|fc_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4db2f3b7081968e3591720e6786d4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S5\\S5_SCENE_KIT_BOUNDARY_CONCEPT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 329 \n 330 Therefore V1 must include explicit production boundaries such as:\n 331 - allowed generation modes\n 332 - kit complexity ceiling\n-333 - motion budget or motion allowed flag\n+333 - a simple motion policy\n 334 - baseline asset count expectations\n 335 \n+336 For V1, motion should be handled through a deterministic system rule rather than open-ended LLM choice.\n+337 The current preferred policy is:\n+338 - `motion_policy: first_10_scenes_only`\n+339 - scenes with index `<= 10` receive `motion_allowed = true`\n+340 - scenes after that receive `motion_allowed = false`\n+341 \n+342 This should be injected by the substrate or boundary logic rather than freely invented by S5.\n+343 \n 336 ### 9.4 Preserve grounding while allowing controlled freedom\n 337 \n 338 Not all asset families need the same grounding level.\n 339 \n     ...\n 370 - grounding baseline for the video\n 371 - global constraints all scenes must respect\n 372 - generation budget posture for the whole video\n 373 - allowed generation modes\n-374 - whether motion is allowed and at what budget level\n+382 - whether motion is allowed under the active deterministic motion policy\n 375 \n 376 ### 10.2 What V1 should explicitly avoid\n 377 \n 378 V1 should **not** attempt full detailed modeling of:\n     ...\n 468 S5 must design kits that S6 can realistically materialize.\n 469 \n 470 This means the conceptual boundary must include practical production constraints such as:\n 471 - `allowed_generation_modes`\n-472 - `motion_allowed`\n-473 - `motion_budget`\n+480 - `motion_policy`\n+481 - `motion_allowed` (injected deterministically per scene rather than freely authored by the LLM)\n 474 - `kit_complexity_ceiling`\n 475 - high-level asset count guidance\n 476 \n 477 Without these, S5 risks becoming a purely aspirational planner.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":333},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775557431215}}
{"type":"message","id":"da22ce5c","parentId":"31bd9e92","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:24:00.777Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_M7dkc4NW1zuK2a4umNi2cAaI|fc_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4db3b3fd081969bbc729ec06c0cb1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S5\\S5_SCENE_KIT_OBJECTS_V1.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- `motion_allowed`\n  - boolean\n- `motion_budget`\n  - example values: `none`, `low`, `medium`, `high`\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\n","newText":"- `motion_policy`\n  - example values: `first_10_scenes_only`\n- `motion_allowed`\n  - boolean, injected deterministically per scene from the active motion policy rather than authored freely by the LLM\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\n"},{"oldText":"- `allowed_generation_modes[]`\n  - optional scene-level restriction or override within global limits\n- `motion_allowed`\n  - optional scene-level value\n- `motion_priority`\n  - example values: `none`, `optional`, `preferred`\n- `scene_budget_posture`\n","newText":"- `allowed_generation_modes[]`\n  - optional scene-level restriction or override within global limits\n- `motion_allowed`\n  - boolean injected deterministically by the substrate from the active motion policy; not a free scene-level decision by the S5 LLM\n- `scene_budget_posture`\n"},{"oldText":"Together, these objects shift the pipeline away from early rigid scene closure and toward a structured, grounded, editorially usable scene kit model.\n","newText":"Together, these objects shift the pipeline away from early rigid scene closure and toward a structured, grounded, editorially usable scene kit model.\n\nA practical V1 simplification also applies here:\n- motion should not be treated as an open-ended scene-level planning variable\n- instead, `motion_allowed` should be determined by system policy and injected into the scene context\n- the currently preferred policy is `motion_policy: first_10_scenes_only`\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S5\\\\S5_SCENE_KIT_OBJECTS_V1.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"- `motion_allowed`\\n  - boolean\\n- `motion_budget`\\n  - example values: `none`, `low`, `medium`, `high`\\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\\n\",\"newText\":\"- `motion_policy`\\n  - example values: `first_10_scenes_only`\\n- `motion_allowed`\\n  - boolean, injected deterministically per scene from the active motion policy rather than authored freely by the LLM\\n- `kit_complexity_ceiling`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- `allowed_generation_modes[]`\\n  - optional scene-level restriction or override within global limits\\n- `motion_allowed`\\n  - optional scene-level value\\n- `motion_priority`\\n  - example values: `none`, `optional`, `preferred`\\n- `scene_budget_posture`\\n\",\"newText\":\"- `allowed_generation_modes[]`\\n  - optional scene-level restriction or override within global limits\\n- `motion_allowed`\\n  - boolean injected deterministically by the substrate from the active motion policy; not a free scene-level decision by the S5 LLM\\n- `scene_budget_posture`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"Together, these objects shift the pipeline away from early rigid scene closure and toward a structured, grounded, editorially usable scene kit model.\\n\",\"newText\":\"Together, these objects shift the pipeline away from early rigid scene closure and toward a structured, grounded, editorially usable scene kit model.\\n\\nA practical V1 simplification also applies here:\\n- motion should not be treated as an open-ended scene-level planning variable\\n- instead, `motion_allowed` should be determined by system policy and injected into the scene context\\n- the currently preferred policy is `motion_policy: first_10_scenes_only`\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":245,"output":425,"cacheRead":110080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110750,"cost":{"input":0.000612500