{"type":"message","id":"1ab7f5f9","parentId":"ae7baa88","timestamp":"2026-04-07T10:35:39.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bLux2dbd7WnmbsDxZqdYa7RZ|fc_06eabf5088e8d8890169d4dde01a0c81968b46291d9c6d4cb7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\OpenClaw Workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S5\\S5_ASSET_FAMILY_GRAMMAR_V1_DRAFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### `editorial_affordance`\nA lightweight indicator of how this family is likely to help downstream editorial work.\n\nProposed V1 values:\n- `hold`\n- `insert`\n- `sequence`\n- `bridge`\n- `contrast`\n\nThese values are intentionally light.\nThey are not a full editorial grammar.\nThey only provide enough signal to help downstream thinking.\n\n### `editorial_notes`\nShort free-text note on how the family is likely to be useful in the cut.\n\nThis is preferable to adding many more enums too early.\n","newText":"### `editorial_notes`\nA lightweight free-text note on how this family is likely to be useful in the cut.\n\nIn the current preferred V1 direction, the editorial layer should remain textual rather than enum-heavy.\nThat means:\n- no separate closed editorial role taxonomy is required yet\n- no heavy editorial affordance system is required yet\n- the family keeps its production-facing `family_type`\n- downstream/editorial nuance is expressed through concise text\n\nThis is preferable in V1 because it is:\n- easier for LLMs to generate naturally\n- easier to interpret in context\n- less brittle than forcing prematurely rigid editorial enums\n"},{"oldText":"  - `detail`\n  - `atmospheric`\n  - `transition`\n  - `fallback`\n\nThese values are intentionally modest.\nThey are expressive enough for V1 without becoming taxonomically heavy.\n","newText":"  - `detail`\n  - `atmospheric`\n  - `transition`\n  - `fallback`\n\nThese values are intentionally modest.\nThey are expressive enough for V1 without becoming taxonomically heavy.\nThey also replace the need for a second competing family-role taxonomy in V1.\n"},{"oldText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f1\nfamily_type: hero\npriority: required\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 2\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\n  - regeneration_from_reference\nreference_inputs:\n  - patton_face_reference_01\n  - patton_uniform_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - facial identity of George S. Patton\n  - correct military uniform cues\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid exact source framing\neditorial_affordance: hold\neditorial_notes: Primary identity anchor for the scene.\n```","newText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f1\nfamily_type: hero\npriority: required\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 2\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\n  - regeneration_from_reference\nreference_inputs:\n  - patton_face_reference_01\n  - patton_uniform_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - facial identity of George S. Patton\n  - correct military uniform cues\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid exact source framing\neditorial_notes: Primary identity anchor for the scene; should sustain an opening or emphasis beat.\n```"},{"oldText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f2\nfamily_type: support\npriority: preferred\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 2\n  ideal: 3\n  maximum: 4\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\nreference_inputs:\n  - quitandinha_facade_01\n  - quitandinha_architecture_detail_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - recognizable Hotel Quitandinha architecture\n  - key facade and structure cues\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid repetitive angle duplication\neditorial_affordance: sequence\neditorial_notes: Support progression from grounded establishing into richer architectural coverage.\n```","newText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f2\nfamily_type: support\npriority: preferred\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 2\n  ideal: 3\n  maximum: 4\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\nreference_inputs:\n  - quitandinha_facade_01\n  - quitandinha_architecture_detail_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - recognizable Hotel Quitandinha architecture\n  - key facade and structure cues\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid repetitive angle duplication\neditorial_notes: Support progression from grounded establishing into richer architectural coverage.\n```"},{"oldText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f3\nfamily_type: detail\npriority: preferred\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 3\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\nreference_inputs:\n  - tiger1_profile_01\n  - tiger1_turret_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - Tiger I silhouette\n  - correct turret/body structure\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid genericizing into an unspecified tank\neditorial_affordance: insert\neditorial_notes: Factual machine-specific reinforcement.\n```","newText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f3\nfamily_type: detail\npriority: preferred\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 3\ngrounding_strength: high\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - reference_guided_generation\nreference_inputs:\n  - tiger1_profile_01\n  - tiger1_turret_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - Tiger I silhouette\n  - correct turret/body structure\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid genericizing into an unspecified tank\neditorial_notes: Factual machine-specific reinforcement.\n```"},{"oldText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f4\nfamily_type: atmospheric\npriority: required\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 3\ngrounding_strength: low\ncreative_freedom_level: open\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - from_scratch_generation\n  - multi_reference_synthesis\nreference_inputs:\n  - imperial_hall_reference_01\n  - decay_texture_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - tonal coherence with the rest of the video\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid heavy-handed symbolic cliché\neditorial_affordance: contrast\neditorial_notes: Symbolic emotional expansion of the scene.\n```","newText":"```yaml\nfamily_id: f4\nfamily_type: atmospheric\npriority: required\ntarget_asset_count:\n  minimum: 1\n  ideal: 2\n  maximum: 3\ngrounding_strength: low\ncreative_freedom_level: open\npreferred_generation_modes:\n  - from_scratch_generation\n  - multi_reference_synthesis\nreference_inputs:\n  - imperial_hall_reference_01\n  - decay_texture_reference_02\npreserve_requirements:\n  - tonal coherence with the rest of the video\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\n  - avoid heavy-handed symbolic cliché\neditorial_notes: Symbolic emotional expansion of the scene.\n```"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\OpenClaw Workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S5\\\\S5_ASSET_FAMILY_GRAMMAR_V1_DRAFT.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### `editorial_affordance`\\nA lightweight indicator of how this family is likely to help downstream editorial work.\\n\\nProposed V1 values:\\n- `hold`\\n- `insert`\\n- `sequence`\\n- `bridge`\\n- `contrast`\\n\\nThese values are intentionally light.\\nThey are not a full editorial grammar.\\nThey only provide enough signal to help downstream thinking.\\n\\n### `editorial_notes`\\nShort free-text note on how the family is likely to be useful in the cut.\\n\\nThis is preferable to adding many more enums too early.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### `editorial_notes`\\nA lightweight free-text note on how this family is likely to be useful in the cut.\\n\\nIn the current preferred V1 direction, the editorial layer should remain textual rather than enum-heavy.\\nThat means:\\n- no separate closed editorial role taxonomy is required yet\\n- no heavy editorial affordance system is required yet\\n- the family keeps its production-facing `family_type`\\n- downstream/editorial nuance is expressed through concise text\\n\\nThis is preferable in V1 because it is:\\n- easier for LLMs to generate naturally\\n- easier to interpret in context\\n- less brittle than forcing prematurely rigid editorial enums\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"  - `detail`\\n  - `atmospheric`\\n  - `transition`\\n  - `fallback`\\n\\nThese values are intentionally modest.\\nThey are expressive enough for V1 without becoming taxonomically heavy.\\n\",\"newText\":\"  - `detail`\\n  - `atmospheric`\\n  - `transition`\\n  - `fallback`\\n\\nThese values are intentionally modest.\\nThey are expressive enough for V1 without becoming taxonomically heavy.\\nThey also replace the need for a second competing family-role taxonomy in V1.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"```yaml\\nfamily_id: f1\\nfamily_type: hero\\npriority: required\\ntarget_asset_count:\\n  minimum: 1\\n  ideal: 2\\n  maximum: 2\\ngrounding_strength: high\\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\\npreferred_generation_modes:\\n  - reference_guided_generation\\n  - regeneration_from_reference\\nreference_inputs:\\n  - patton_face_reference_01\\n  - patton_uniform_reference_02\\npreserve_requirements:\\n  - facial identity of George S. Patton\\n  - correct military uniform cues\\navoid_literal_copy_notes:\\n  - avoid exact source framing\\neditorial_affordance: hold\\neditorial_notes: Primary identity anchor for the scene.\\n```\",\"newText\":\"```yaml\\nfamily_id: f1\\nfamily_type: hero\\npriority: required\\ntarget_asset_count:\\n  minimum: 1\\n  ideal: 2\\n  maximum: 2\\ngrounding_strength: high\\ncreative_freedom_level: controlled\\npreferred_generation_modes:\\n  - reference_guided_generation\\n  - regeneration_from_reference\\nreference_inputs:\\n  - patton_face_reference_01\\n  - patton_uniform_reference_02\\npreserve_requirements:\\n  - facial identity of George S. Patton\\n  - correct military uniform cues\\navoid_literal_copy_notes: